description: Gets information about your Rekognition projects. This operation requires permissions to perform the rekognition:DescribeProjects action.

parameters.name: ProjectNames
parameters.description: A list of the projects that you want Rekognition to describe. If you don't specify a value, the response includes descriptions for all the projects in your AWS account. (string) ---

parameters.name: Features
parameters.description: Specifies the type of customization to filter projects by. If no value is specified, CUSTOM_LABELS is used as a default. (string) ---

nested_items.name: ProjectDescriptions
nested_items.description: A list of project descriptions. The list is sorted by the date and time the projects are created.

nested_items.name: ProjectArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the project.

nested_items.name: CreationTimestamp
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp for the date and time that the project was created.

nested_items.name: Status
nested_items.description: The current status of the project.

nested_items.name: Datasets
nested_items.description: Information about the training and test datasets in the project.

nested_items.name: CreationTimestamp
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp for the date and time that the dataset was created.

nested_items.name: DatasetArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the dataset.

nested_items.name: StatusMessage
nested_items.description: The status message for the dataset.

nested_items.name: StatusMessageCode
nested_items.description: The status message code for the dataset operation. If a service error occurs, try the API call again later. If a client error occurs, check the input parameters to the dataset API call that failed.

nested_items.name: Feature
nested_items.description: Specifies the project that is being customized.

nested_items.name: AutoUpdate
nested_items.description: Indicates whether automatic retraining will be attempted for the versions of the project. Applies only to adapters.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If the previous response was incomplete (because there is more results to retrieve), Amazon Rekognition returns a pagination token in the response. You can use this pagination token to retrieve the next set of results.
